## 5. Risks and Assumptions

### 5.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| Source files change frequently causing bundle to be outdated | Medium | High | Automated sync script + CI/CD pipeline |
| Large bundle size slows extension install | Low | Low | Resources are text files (small), exclude binaries |
| User customizations lost during update | High | Medium | Checksum detection + backup option in Update command |
| Agent prompt files too large for Kiro context window | Medium | Low | Keep prompts focused, split if needed |

### 5.2 Assumptions

* Source project (MCPOrchestration) is the single source of truth for all resources
* All 9 agents are stable and ready for distribution
* Kiro IDE supports .kiro/agents/, .kiro/steering/, .kiro/hooks/ directory conventions
* Document templates use {PLACEHOLDER} variable syntax that agents can fill

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement | Details |
| Build Time | Bundle generation < 5 seconds | copy-resources.js + gen-checksums.js combined |
| Package Size | VSIX < 5 MB | Text-only resources, no binaries in core bundle |
| Integrity | SHA-256 checksums for all files | Tamper detection via bundled manifest |
| Compatibility | VS Code 1.85+ | Minimum engine version |
| Maintainability | Single sync script updates all resources | sync-from-source.ps1 handles all mappings |

